# Supply-chain hardening: refuse to install any package version published less than 7 days ago. This gives the
# ecosystem a window to detect and yank a compromised release (à la the npm worm / LiteLLM incidents) before it
# can reach a build here. pnpm's `minimumReleaseAge` is in MINUTES — 7 days = 7 × 24 × 60 = 10080.
minimum-release-age=10080
